        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A rare inherited mitochondrial disease characterized by the clinical features of Leber hereditary optic neuropathy in combination with other systemic or neurological abnormalities. These abnormalities include: postural tremor motor disorder multiple sclerosis-like syndrome spinal cord disease skeletal changes Parkinsonism with dystonia anarthria motor and sensory peripheral neuropathy spasticity mild encephalopathy and cardiac arrhythmias."
        },
